The top gate or main entrance on Richards Drive is a well-known fixture for frequent visitors to the property and the Midrand area. In accordance with our commitment to reinvesting in the 32 hectare Gallagher Convention Centre property and facilities, the entrance arch is undergoing refurbishment for an exciting and renewed appearance.427 Square meters of black tiles will be used for recladding the entire entrance. The project commenced in May 2018 and is estimated to be finalised in six weeks.In anticipation of revealing the exciting upgrades to the main entrance, we are happy to share the renderings of what you can expect once the refurbishment has been finalised.<img src="http://biz-file.com/c/1806/444643.jpg" alt="The main gate is getting a makeover" width="300" height="275" rel="">click to enlarge<img src="http://biz-file.com/c/1806/444645.jpg" alt="The main gate is getting a makeover" width="300" height="275" rel="">click to enlarge<img src="http://biz-file.com/c/1806/444648.jpg" alt="The main gate is getting a makeover" width="300" height="275" rel="">click to enlarge